channel.title: Error: loaderror Starting up 20
channel.description:
I was trying to convert my client into a webclient, and everything went well. So I jarred my client, and ran the jar, and got this error after the cache downloaded: [img]http://i739.photobucket.com/albums/xx32/float1234/Capture.jpg[/img] So, I was eager to find out what could have caused this, so I went back into my webclient folder and ran the .bat file that starts up the client, and I got this error in the CMD prompt: Error: loaderror Starting up 20
Please help! I don't have any money, so all I can do is rep++.

item.title: Error: loaderror Starting up 20
item.dc:creator: @zyle1992 Zymus
item.description:
@zyle1992 wrote:

loaderror 20 means that it was trying to connect to the webserver to check if the cache files were correct, and since there is no webserver running, it can’t check, so it throws an error.

Read full topic

item.title: Error: loaderror Starting up 20
item.dc:creator: @Loveandpower Loveandpower
item.description:
@Loveandpower wrote:

[quote=“Tutorial, post:3, topic:396049”][quote author=Loveandpower link=topic=493229.msg3606001#msg3606001 date=1306113485]
Did you add any custom .dat files?
[/quote]
The only thing I changed cache wise was the crowns, and I used Tom’s Cache Suite.

Edit: I deleted the cache from my C:/ directory, and I got this error after downloading the cache: Error: loaderror Finished downloading cache.zip! 35
But, I exited out, and ran again, and got the error in the topic’s title.[/quote]I got a similar error when I messed with my model header on an older pi so maybe it was some sort of header.
